  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager",
  "description": "<h5><strong>RESPONSIBILITY:</strong></h5>\n<h5>Drive product success by bringing the product to users</h5>\n<ul>\n  <li>Partner with product manager and designers to conduct user Interviews.</li>\n  <li>Partner with product manager to run sprint plannings, scrums,<br>\nretrospectives.</li>\n  <li>Track and manage development pace to ensure timely delivery.</li>\n  <li>Conduct and support thorough systems, users, and security tests pre-release.</li>\n  <li>Run user education campaigns to drive product adoption post-release.</li>\n  <li>Provide product support and work with product/engineering to identify and fix bugs.</li>\n</ul>\n<h5><strong>EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS NEEDED:</strong></h5>\n<ul>\n  <li>Experience in building digital products.</li>\n  <li>Proven track record of delivering effective products with limited resources.</li>\n  <li>End to end experience working with product team to build products.</li>\n  <li>Strong written and verbal communication skills, including documentation, minute taking and technical writing.</li>\n  <li>Highly meticulous and tenacious, follows up with things to closure.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work effectively and independently under pressure and prioritize effectively to meet tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Certifications like Scrum Master, Product Owner, Business Analysis<br>\nProfessional are a plus.</li>\n  <li>Computer science, product management related degrees or diplomas are a plus.</li>\n  <li>Experience with platforms like Confluence, JIRA, Balsamiq are a plus.</li>\n</ul>",
